Mpact Ltd. (MPT)  rose to the highest level
since it was spun out of Mondi Ltd. in July after the South
African packaging company reported a 6.4 percent increase in
operating profit.  The stock climbed 3.3 percent, to 15.50 rand at the close
in Johannesburg, the biggest gain and the strongest price since
the companyâ€™s shares started trading on July 11  Operating profit excluding one-time items advanced to 516.5
million rand ($69 million) in the 12 months through December,
the company said in a statement. Mpact declared a maiden
dividend of 40 cents a share.  To contact the reporter on this story:
